cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software, the calibrated model, or the
  benchmark-integrity harness (contamination probe, blinding protocol,
  sim-lift grader) in an academic work, please cite both the paper and
  the software.
title: >-
  DigitalTwinSim — A Calibrated LLM-Conditioned Agent-Based Model
  of Public Opinion Dynamics
abstract: >-
  Calibrated LLM-conditioned agent-based model of public opinion
  dynamics with hierarchical Bayesian calibration (SVI + NUTS),
  online assimilation via Ensemble Kalman Filter, a four-axis LLM
  data-contamination probe, a deterministic title/country/date/agent
  blinding protocol, and an apples-to-apples null-baseline sim-lift
  grader (DTW / KS / RMSE / terminal error, Diebold–Mariano with
  HLN correction against persistence / AR(1) / linear-trend / mean
  baselines).
type: software
version: 2.8.0
date-released: "2026-05-03"
